<header class="hero short">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow"><span class="dot"></span> About · Two founders · Operator-led</span>
      <h1>We're operators first.<br/><em>Consultants by accident.</em></h1>
      <p class="lede">Lighter Fluid was founded in 2024 as a generalist studio. By 2026, the work that mattered most was the AI operating systems we'd been building for our own businesses — and for the enterprise clients one of us had been advising for years before that. So that's what we sell now.</p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <div class="prose">
        <p>This site, our process, and the framework library all came from the same place: trying to run three businesses with the systems available in 2024 and finding them inadequate. The skills we build for clients are the skills we built for ourselves first. The standards documents we install are the standards we wrote for our own teams.</p>

        <p>That's the only honest claim we can make in 2026. We don't have a long client roster yet. We have three businesses we built, the operating playbook those businesses run on, and a strong opinion that this playbook compounds when other operators install it.</p>

        <p class="pullquote">
          We sound like operators describing what they actually built. Not consultants pitching what they could.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ============ FOUNDERS ============ -->
  <section class="section sm rule">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-head">
        <span class="label">The founders</span>
        <h2>Two operators.<br/><em>Different specialties.<br/>Same shop.</em></h2>
      </div>

      <div class="founders">
        <article class="founder">
          <div class="portrait">[ Portrait — Gabe ]</div>
          <h3>Gabe Coyne</h3>
          <span class="role">Founder · Operator</span>
          <p>Co-founded Influence Mobile and helped grow it into the third-largest mobile ad network in the world by revenue ($200M+ lifetime revenue, 100M+ app installs delivered). Co-founded Stix Golf in 2020 — $8M year one, $100M+ lifetime sales, through Series A and Series B. Currently CEO of Host Modern, $4.5M in year one with a 10%+ profit margin.</p>
          <p>Before Influence Mobile, ran a creative-services studio in Seattle for over a decade. After exiting Influence Mobile, was a partner at Prota Ventures in Chicago — a venture studio doing innovation consulting for Exelon, ADP, and Citi Bank. The Prota work was the prototype for what Lighter Fluid does now: take a client's idea through design, prototype, validation, launch, and scale, and document the system enough that the client team can keep running it.</p>
          <p>The mobile-ad-network background is where the technical instincts come from — attribution under noise, real-time decisioning, fraud detection. The DTC background is where the operating playbook came from. The Prota background is where the consulting discipline came from.</p>
          <p style="margin-top:18px;"><a class="inline-link" href="mailto:gabe@lighterfluid.co">gabe@lighterfluid.co</a></p>
        </article>

        <article class="founder">
          <div class="portrait">[ Portrait — Collin ]</div>
          <h3>Collin Duff</h3>
          <span class="role">Co-Founder · Operator</span>
          <p>Head of Product at Stix Golf. COO of Host Modern through its launch. Co-founder of Viator Coffee. The product-and-ops counterweight to Gabe's growth-and-systems instinct.</p>
          <p>Owns the work that doesn't fit cleanly in a skill — the new product evaluation framework at Stix, the SEO landing page program at Host Modern, the Shopify autopilot loop that auto-deploys low-risk fixes from a Slack channel. If a client engagement involves shipping product or fixing a stack-deep operational gap, Collin runs it.</p>
          <p style="margin-top:18px;"><a class="inline-link" href="mailto:collin@lighterfluid.co">collin@lighterfluid.co</a></p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
