  <!-- ============ HOW WE WORK TOGETHER ============ -->
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <div class="prose">
        <h2>How we work together — and with you</h2>
        <p>We're a partnership, not an agency. Two principals on every engagement. No account manager layer. The person who builds your skill is the person who explains it back to your team. The person who scopes your engagement is the person who presents it.</p>
        <p>We won't take on more work than the two of us can do honestly. That caps how many engagements we run at once. It also caps the size of the company we're building. We're fine with both.</p>

        <h2>What we believe</h2>
        <p><em>Operators understand operators.</em> Most consulting fails because the consultant has never had to live with the recommendation. Every framework in our library exists because we hit the wall it solves. The Apr 2026 UTC timezone bug at Host Modern wasn't theoretical — it inverted a ROAS read in a real morning meeting and we had to explain it. The data validation framework exists because of that morning.</p>

        <p><em>Standards beat strategy.</em> Strategy decks compound badly. Standards documents compound well. Every framework we install is one a client team can extend without us. That's the whole product.</p>

        <p><em>Speed without panic.</em> AI lets you ship faster. It also lets you ship faster in the wrong direction. The frameworks exist to keep speed and rigor compatible — batch architecture so you don't burn budget, source-of-truth hierarchy so you don't act on bad numbers, tier evaluation so you don't over-trust low-volume signal.</p>

        <p><em>Documented or it didn't ship.</em> A skill that runs but isn't documented is a skill that breaks the day a model deprecates. We treat documentation as half the deliverable, and we charge accordingly.</p>

        <h2>What we won't do</h2>
        <p>We won't take engagements that compromise the partnership cap (more than four active engagements at once). We won't hire a junior team to scale. We won't sell hours. We won't write the deck and disappear. We won't pitch industries where the operator credibility doesn't transfer.</p>

        <p>If those constraints fit your need, the first call is free. If they don't, we'll happily refer you to consultancies that fit better. There are good ones — the AI consulting market is bigger than us.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

